Made a new Q&A thread since the last one filled up. Here are the rules again for reference:

  • Someone number his questions, as QX.
  • And another will answer that question with AX.
  • If the answer isn't enough satisfying, repeat your question as QXbis/ter, add an answer with AXbis/ter, or even QX.Y/AX.Y etc.

Example:
player1Q13. ?player2A13. .player1Q13a or Q13bis or Q13.1. ?player3A13a or A13bis or A13.1.

This is a thread for helping each other on short questions that shouldn't need multiple answers nor debate. If you want to debate, create a new topic for it.

Check Acid Blood Formula

[895738]
BlackAndLokiA28: addition
I don't know why you will need regression when the simple gathering of data and estimation of probability would be enough, but we are not speaking about confirmed or statistically checked info, it is rather a "feeling". I (and few other players) tried on 3 servers and it was always so that Archelion around tunnel spawned much faster (we used irmas). We share our feeling with community. I will not claim it is really so and not a coincidence, but those who want can try. Even if the chance is the same it will not make situation worse.

No, you misunderstood me by taking the word "regresion" out of its contextual phrase. Regression to the mean is when you test a theory like this by building up a large sample of data. It can be as simple as a flipping a coin. The more times you flip that coin, the more evenly distributed the number of heads and tails you will get. For example, you flip a coin 10 times and you get 8 heads and 2 tails. Well, it looks like you usually get heads when you flip a coin. No, flip it 100 times, and you'll get something like 53 heads and 47 tails. Keep going until the number of heads and tails is even. That's known as regression to the mean. I could spam the coin flip emoticon here to make my point but I'll probably get in trouble by the mods for doing it.

If you test the spawn rates about 100 times and there's a large percentage of spawns when you think they often spawn, then I stand corrected. If not, then there's no pattern or correlation. I don't mind other players giving it a try if they think 1Lsks's confirmation is satisfactory. We are dealing with chance and some people might not be so lucky and might ridicule that confirmation. The larger the sample and the higher the percentage spawn rate, the stronger the confirmation.

Q65: How does Rencarnation skill work and should I use it with Etherwasps, Hippoclamps or Smogs?
On december 29, 2014
mtp85

A65: When the Dinoz dies (at least level 40), you will have an option to Reincarnate instead of Revive. It will be reset to level 1, with no status items except any it started with (Demon, mostly) and a new one indicating it's Reincarnated. All missions done can be repeated, and any spheres used are lost.

It also starts with 5 additional random elements (but not skills). I believe (but can't prove) that it's based on the Dinoz grid, so you won't get on an Etherwasp or on a Smog.

I wouldn't either of those 3 specifically to get Reincarnation - but I'd use it if they didn't turn out like you wanted.

By based on the grid, I just meant more likely to get their main element, if they have one.

On march 28, 2015
[895738]
DainlyQ121: what does a speed of an element do? like lighning attack= increases lightning speed attacks by %40 so? higher chance of using a lightning skill?BlackAndLokiA 121
read here

A121: Loki's answer only covers what speed an init do, but not specifically the speed of an element, even though it can be inferred from loki's answer.

Basically, Dainly, if you have an elemental speed buff/penalty, it will only occur when you carry out that respective element assault. Examples:

dinoz with adrenaline and lightning attack have double speed when they use their assault. An A skill doesn't replace that. After the attack, it returns to normal.

dinoz that have EF have to get the speed penalties. Once they launch an assault, their speed is cut by around 66% in total because their opponents in both pve and pvp can do up to 3 attacks in a row before the EF dino can move again. After the assault, their speed returns to its base level.
On march 28, 2015
BlackAndLoki
sendosBasically, Dainly, if you have an elemental speed buff/penalty, it will only occur when you carry out that respective element assault. Examples:

What you say is wrong.
The penalties or bonuses do not apply upon on the assault of that element, but upon on the any event that happened at the moment when considered element triggered at the element cycle. So if you have triggered a fire A-skill instead of lightning assault at the moment when lighting was on your element cycle, you still get the speed bonuses from lightning skills after that fire A-skill.

Q177 Anyone knows if with fear factor a dinoz leader of 5 brave its possible for the another 4 dinoz to join him?
On october 15, 2015
Bengeldorn

A177: FF has two effects:
1. If your brave dino is leading, any number of dinos can join him, as like he would not be brave.
2. If your brave dino is following, you can follow any dino, that has at least 1 point in an starting element*, as your brave dino with FF has.

For example: If you have a brave dino with fear factor, 2 dinos can follow it.
If this dinos has charisma, sympathethic or Aphrodisia, the number increases for each skill it has.
If you want to have brave dinos follow another brave dino, each brave dino (follower and leader) needs a FF.


* Points from reincarnation don't count.

Totoru

A194
b, leagues have nothing to do with this.

c, The ranking is for clans, not players. On the reward distribution day every clan get the rewards according to their placement, thus every member of the clan gets the same rewards. Since your reward depends on your actual clan, you can only get 1 or 0 set of rewards.

For examle: You were in clan A for 3 rounds, then spent the rest of the tournament in clan B. At the rewarding day, you'll get the same rewards as everyone in clan B, even if clan A ranked higher, since you're not part of that clan. Same logic, if you quit Clan B before rewarding, you'll not get anything either from A or B. So only your current clan's rank counts at the moment of reward distribution.

A 234: You can setup a link and click it multiple times to use a note in your inventory (I've got it as a link on my bookmarks toolbar in chrome entitled "Gold" ):
